data.description: 2510 Pemberton Creek is composed of 5.07 acres (Lots 9 and 10) located in the highly sought-after Pemberton Creek subdivision. Make this timeless ranch home, stable, and fenced riding acreage yours. The home at 2510 Pemberton Creek Dr is a unique, one of a kind a Spanish hacienda styled home with Asian influences noted in the decorative gates, arched driveway entrance, and the Asian fly away styled tiled roof. Indeed, this 2-story, 2,724 sq. ft. 3-bedroom, 3-bath home has some unique features: a combination formal living room with a raise dining room, a 1st floor office, large kitchen, and a family room that spans across the back of the home and overlooks the covered back porch, pool, and spacious pool decking. There is a pool bath and utility room too. Nestled into the left side of the house and pool area is a picturesque pond. The inviting open upper balcony overlooks the pond, pool, and stable acreage and has been reinforced by a Thermoplastic Polyolefin roofing membrane. Extensive flashing was added to the roof area and chimney. Other recent improvements include a totally renovated kitchen, new flooring both upstairs and downstairs, and bathroom renovations too. The pool has been resurfaced. A water softener and filtration system has been added to the home. But there is more! Further back from the home site is a stable with 7 stalls and a tack room. Groom and ride your horses on the fully fenced 2.32 acre adjacent to the home. Another option is to add to your ranch by building another home on lot 10. This property is an idea location since it is located just off Muck Pond Road at the McIntosh I-4 exit. It has easy access to downtown Tampa, Brandon, Lakeland and an executive airport nearby. Seffner is a gateway suburban haven for commuters. It is noted for large oak trees, strawberry farms, and lakes, yet it offers the city life of Tampa. See floor plan & site plan attached and call today for a tour.
